headline: U.S. Bank: Truck Freight Picks up in Northeast, Drops Sharply in Southwest
summary: MINNEAPOLIS, May 01, 2025--During the first three months of the year, U.S. truck freight volume was down 5.8% while spending was off 2.5% compared to the fourth quarter, according to the latest U.S. Bank Freight Payment Index. Performance varied widely among regions, with Southwest volume down 21.2% quarterly while Northeast shipments increased 3.6%.
